     <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Solved Problem: </strong></span>If the adult dose for a drug is 70 mg per day. 
     What dose should be given to a child with a BSA of 0.33 m<sup>2</sup>?</p>
     <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Approach: </strong></span>Using the above equation, calculate the required dose.</p>
     <div class="formulae"> <p> $$ Patient's \ Dose = { 0.33 \ (m^2) \over 1.73 \ m^2 } \times 70 \ (mg) $$</p></div>
     <p><span style="color: black"><strong>Answer: </strong></span>13.4 mg</p>
